This paper involves the use of Reinforcement Learning and deep neural networks to build a profitable electronic trading agent. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of AI techniques to learn a temporal and causal representation of the market, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of a model-based approach to predict market movement and trade impact, which makes cs.TR (Trading and Market Microstructure) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a self-supervised approach to train the agent, which makes cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) another likely category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a simulator to predict market movement, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another likely category.
